body:
Verilator revision befb415f278af51fc3ecc3dda1dfe820de023bd1, but the bug affects all v5 versions and some earlier ones.

Test case:
```systemverilog
// verilator lint_off MULTIDRIVEN
module t(input clk);
  initial begin
    $dumpfile("dump.vcd");
    $dumpvars;
  end

  logic [31:0] lhs1, lhs2, rhs;

  always_comb lhs1 = rhs;
  assign lhs2 = rhs;

  always @(posedge clk) rhs = '1;

  always @(negedge clk) begin
    release lhs1;
    release lhs2;
  end
endmodule
```

Waveform:

![caliptra-bug-master](https://github.com/chipsalliance/caliptra-rtl/assets/9216518/f01abcaa-f9e1-495e-be47-1f7f7e9d456c)

`lhs1` and `lhs2` are oscillating for some reason, when they should equal `rhs`.

The `always_comb` bug also appears on v4.228.

![caliptra-bug-4 228](https://github.com/chipsalliance/caliptra-rtl/assets/9216518/08fedc7a-fe8e-417d-b763-bdc19693274d)

This seems to be causing a regression in Caliptra: https://github.com/chipsalliance/caliptra-rtl/issues/79
